      "content": "Even a single dose of ibuprofen can be a problem if you have CKD, because it can put extra strain on your kidneys. For a quick fix, you should absolutely try to get some immediate, non-drug relief, like a cold compress or a nice long rest. If you absolutely must take something, try to keep the dose minimal, but honestly, the best thing is to get that prescription-level advice from a professional.",
